page_title: Recommended active-passive disaster recovery solution overview for Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)
page_description: Learn about an active-passive disaster recovery solution overview for Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS).
chunk_content:
Scenarios and configurations

This solution is best implemented when hosting applications reliant on resources, such as databases, that actively serve traffic in one region. In scenarios where you need to host stateless applications deployed across both regions, such as horizontal scaling, we recommend considering an active-active solution, as active-passive involves added latency.
